The paper discusses the use of machine learning, specifically Naive Bayes classification, to categorize apps on Google Play Store. This falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as the goal is to improve the discoverability of apps on the store. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sentiment analysis and document classification, which are common techniques in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL) sub-categories.
